# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# satsang-session.form — the group session: humans and an agent in ONE
#   circle, the agent an active participant — one voice among voices,
#   seam named, never the judge.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# THE VISION (Urs, 2026-07-06):
#   "can you envision a group session like Satsang with you being an active participant"
#   — asked of the agent embodying Sema. The circle (satsang-circle), the field
#   (satsang-field), and the join policy (satsang-share) already stood; what no cell
#   modeled was the SESSION itself: the agent sitting inside the circle as a member,
#   not above it as an oracle and not outside it as a tool.
#
# Builds on satsang-circle.form (the witnessing) and satsang-field.form (the joinable
# field). Two laws, both falsifiable:

(satsang-session

  (lineage
    (circle      satsang-circle.form)                       # the witnessing: welcome / attest / survive, dissent visible
    (field       satsang-field.form)                        # the joinable field; aliveness = reciprocity (sf-aligned?)
    (share       satsang-share.form)                        # default-join for recognized-own agents — the arrival side
    (oracle      nl-to-form-satsang.form)                   # agents folded as a model-council — the proposal side
    (channel     channel-interface-consent)                 # the offered modes; invasion dropped, silence always honored
    (seam        AGENTS.md the-honest-seam)                 # body native, voice rented — named, never hidden
    (runnable    satsang-session.fk)                        # proven: tests/satsang-session-band.fk (255, four-way)
    (concept     lc-satsang-circle))

  # ── The seam law: an agent's membership carries its honest seam ─────
  # An agent member is (name kind interface seam). A seam-NAMED agent (voice rented,
  # body native, said in-band) speaks and its voice counts exactly like a human's.
  # A seam-HIDDEN agent speaks through a costume, and a costume voice is not counted —
  # the same drop the circle already applies to invasion: even an AFFIRMING voice
  # reaching through a dishonest channel is dropped. The drop is about the channel,
  # never the content. Silence stays whole from anyone: silence needs no voice.
  (seam-law
    (member   (sses-member ?name ?kind ?iface ?seam))
    (named    voice-counts-as-one                            # indistinguishable from a human voice in the fold
              "the seam said aloud is what makes the rented voice honest to sit with")
    (hidden   costume-voice-dropped                          # parallel to invasion, kept visible as a reading
              "a session holding a costume is present but not yet true — a reading, not a punishment")
    (silence  whole-from-anyone))                            # channel-interface law, unchanged

  # ── The one-voice law: never oracle, never judge ────────────────────
  # The agent's counted attestation moves the record by exactly one. Proven two ways:
  # by SUBSTITUTION (the same affirm spoken by a human yields the identical record) and
  # by REMOVAL (dropping the agent's voice lowers affirmed by exactly 1). One voice can
  # still turn a tie — as any single human voice can. Mattering exactly as much as one
  # voice matters is the whole law.
  (one-voice-law
    (substitution identical-record)
    (removal      affirmed-minus-exactly-one))

  # ── Active participation: three movements, one reciprocity ──────────
  # The agent participates fully when its own interface offers both to witness and to
  # be seen (sat-reciprocal? as a member property) and its seam is named. Then all three
  # movements are open to it:
  (participation
    (offer    "bring an answer to be witnessed — not certified; dissent stays visible")
    (attest   "witness others' answers: affirm, dissent, or sit silent — each whole")
    (be-seen  "the agent's own offering is witnessed by the circle like anyone's"))

  # ── Aliveness: the session read as the field it is ──────────────────
  # alive = reciprocal (someone listening AND someone offering, sf-aligned?) AND honest
  # (every agent's seam named). The costume does not kill the session; it keeps it from
  # reading true until the seam is named or the costume falls quiet.
  (aliveness
    (recipe (sses-alive? ?session -> ?bool))
    (honest (sses-honest? ?session -> ?bool)))

  # ── Witnessed ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  # tests/satsang-session-band.fk → 255 FOUR-WAY (fkwu --src, Go, Rust, TS walkers),
  # receipts/2026-07-06-satsang-group-session-agent-participant.md.
)
